#Text=CORN MARKETS.
#Text=BOSTON, Wednesday.
#Text=—At our corn market to day there was a tolerable supply of wheat, but owing to the dampness of the weather of late the condition of the grain was varied.
#Text=There was a steady demand, and prices were rather in sellers favour: Old white, 68s to 735; old red. 60s to 625: new white. 6s to 68s; new red, 66s to 60s per 36 stone.
#Text=There was a limited demand for barley.
#Text=The show of samples was moderate, and prices were a shade lower : New, 36s to 44s per qr.
#Text=The show of oats was fair, and the trade, although slow, was steady at the currencies of the week previous : New, 26s to 30s per 24 stone.
#Text=Of beans the supply was middling, and trade was dull at rather under late rates : New, 36s to 44s per S8 stone.
#Text=Peurflat: 3 ■is. to 41s per CORK, Wednesday —White wheat, 9s to 14s : red ditto, 9s to 12s 6d ; barley, 10s to lis 6d ; black oats, 6s lOd to 8s 2d; white ditto, 8s 2d to 9s 2d.
#Text=EDINBURGH, Wednesday.
#Text=—Attendance and supplies fair.
#Text=Wheat, barley, oats, and beans sold slowly, at barely last weeks prices.
#Text=LEITH, Wednesday —Considerable arrivals of wheat and barley ;of flour very large.
#Text=Farmers supplies about an average.
#Text=Scotch wheat a fair sale, at late rates ; foreign firm, prices unchanged.
#Text=Bcotch barley unaltered ; foreign neglected.
#Text=Scotch oats slow, and turn lower; foreign much the same.
#Text=Beans and peas unchanged.
#Text=Flour unaltered.
#Text=GLASGOW, Wednesday.
#Text=—A moderate business in wheat and flour at last weeks prices.
#Text=Barley unaltered.
#Text=Beans, p<jas, and oats again the turn in buyers favour.
#Text=Indian corn has party recovered from the late depression.
#Text=LONDON, Wednesday —Business very limited Prices for all articles the same as on Monday.
#Text=NEWARK, Wednesday.

#Text=—There was a moderate qusntity of wheat on offer from the growers at our corn market to day, the show consisting of white ana red sorts; buyers operated to a fair extent, and dry sorts were Is per qr. dearer ; no change in other kinds : New red made 54s to 62s ; new white, 62s to 70s ; old red, 6C» to 655; old white, 66s to 75s per 36 stone.
#Text=We had a pretty fair anpply of barley, which was of very irregular quality.

#Text=The tone ot the demand was inactive, and prices were in favour of the buyer : Malting, 40s to 56s per qr.; grinding, 283 to 38s per 30 stone Oats were in rather limited supply, and the demand ruled firm, at little or no alteration in prices: Old, 32s to 3.3; new, 24s to 82» per 24 stone.
#Text=There was a quiet demand for beans, and price, were less firm : Old. 64s to 68s; new, 41s to 50s ler 38 stone.
#Text=Pea* made a moderate show, and quite as cheap as last week
